Hi Thomas,

I think Karl still reads this list, he and I discussed python NEAT a  
while ago. His version was pretty much feature-complete as of last  
summer, though I haven&#39;t heard anything from him in a while.

I&#39;ve personally coded up a very general NEAT framework in python, but  
I never got around to adding the module for neural networks. My goal  
was basically to abstract away all of the GA code so I could focus on  
different representations (of which I&#39;ve written several, including a  
complexifying GRN, which is similar to NEAT). Anyway if you&#39;re  
interested, the code is fairly well commented (compared to my last  
endeavor :P), and I have stubs completed for adding the remaining  
NEAT bits as a representation, so basically all you&#39;d have to do is  
code up the neural network side. I could also write up a blurb about  
how to add a new representation.

Anyway message me if you&#39;re interested; it might be easier than  
starting from scratch.

-- Joe

